    "name":  "Salmon en Croûte",
    "instructions":  "1. Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the onion; cook until translucent, about 5 minutes. Add the mushrooms and garlic; cook until soft, about 5 minutes. Season with the salt and pepper. Transfer to a bowl. 2. Heat remaining olive oil in the skillet. Add remaining garlic; cook until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Add the spinach; cook until wilted, 3-5 minutes. Season with the salt and pepper. Transfer to another bowl. 3. Preheat oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit (175 degrees Celsius). Line a baking dish with parchment paper. Dust work surface with the flour. Lay 1 puff pastry sheet on it; spread the onion-mushroom mixture over it, leaving a 1/small border. 4. Center salmon on top; sprinkle with the paprika, and top with the spinach. Cover with the second puff pastry sheet. Fold over and crimp edges to seal. Brush with beaten egg. Transfer to the baking dish. 5. Bake in the preheated oven until golden, 40-45 minutes. Cool briefly, then slice into portions. 6. Whisk the mayonnaise, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, and dill together. Spoon sauce onto plates and place a piece of salmon en croûte on each.",
    "simpleInstructions":  "1. Cook onions, mushrooms, and garlic, then set aside. 2. Wilt spinach with the garlic, then set aside. 3. Preheat oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit. 4. Assemble puff pastry with filling and salmon. 5. Bake for 40-45 mins. Meanwhile, mix sauce ingredients. 6. Serve sliced with sauce.",
